data.title: 2024 Summer Olympic Games Central
data.text:
Matt Anderson, Penn State (United States) Photo by Matthew Stockman, Getty Images

ROSEMONT, Ill. – The Big Ten Conference was well represented in Paris by athletes and coaches when the 2024 Summer Olympic Games took place July 24-August 11. A total of 356 athletes had ties to Big Ten Conference institutions, a group consisting of active student-athletes, alumni, transfer students and coaches competing as athletes.

The Big Ten had representation from 64 nations and athletes competing in 17 of 32 sports.

Team USA featured 134 athletes from the Big Ten Conference, which accounted for more than a quarter of the collegiate makeup of the American delegation. The Big Ten was one of only three conferences that had 100 percent school representation on the United States squad. Team USA returned 30 Big Ten medalists for the Paris Games.

A total of 222 Big Ten athletes traveled to Paris for other international delegations. All 18 Big Ten institutions were represented in Paris. In addition, 45 coaches and administrators from the Big Ten made the journey to France.

The Big Ten is also home to 31 Paralympians competing at the Summer Paralympic Games, being held August 28-Sept. 8 in Paris.

Below is the complete list of Big Ten athletes that were selected for the Summer Games:
